==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''cursor'', (runner), from ''[[cursus]]'', perfect passive participle of ''[[currere]]'', (run), + ''[[-or]]'' agentive suffix.  Ultimately from [[PIE]].

=== Noun ===
'''cursor'''

# {{gui}} A moving [[icon]] or other representation of the position of the pointing device.
# {{wordproccessing}} An indicator, often a blinking line or bar, indicating where the next insertion or other edit will take place.
# {{databases}} A reference to a row of data in a [[table]], which moves from row to row as data is [[retrieve]]d by way of it.

